author: @jihoonsong7342
text:
Please touch my heart just once.
It feels so chilly all day long.
Standing beneath a sky colder than winter, even my tears feel like they could freeze.
Please quietly call my name just once, the name you used to say countless times.
Even if I could defy eternity just to see one dayâ€”or even just one minuteâ€”Iâ€™d endure it.
At the end of that wait, I hope youâ€™ll be standing there.

You were like a painting in my memories,
A day I had waited so long for, like a precious gift.
Iâ€™ll cross over time to reach you,
You, who were the first snow in my heart.

Youâ€™ve always felt so distant to me.
Why does that one day with you, that time we shared, hurt me so deeply?
The thought of standing next to you and laughing together brings tears to my eyes,
Because I canâ€™t even imagine it.
If this were a dream, Iâ€™d deliver my heart to you.

You were like a painting in my memories,
A day I had waited so long for, like a precious gift.
Iâ€™ll cross over time to reach you,
You, who were the first snow in my heart.

We cried together and laughed so much.
The time that shone so beautifully and brilliantly, I want to turn it back.

You were like a fleeting day to me,
The time we spent together was breathtakingly beautiful.
Now I whisper a greeting to your lips,
And in your eyes, in your breath, I hold you until I break apart.

Please quietly listen just once,
To the soft echo of my heart.
